rnetes.io/instance: kiali-operator\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      name: kiali-operator\n      namespace: kiali-operator\n      labels:\n        # required for the operator SDK metric service selector\n        name: kiali-operator\n        helm.sh/chart: kiali-operator-1.37.0-SNAPSHOT\n        app: kiali-operator\n        app.kubernetes.io/name: kiali-operator\n        app.kubernetes.io/instance: kiali-operator\n        version: \"v1.37.0-SNAPSHOT\"\n        app.kubernetes.io/version: \"v1.37.0-SNAPSHOT\"\n        app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: Helm\n        app.kubernetes.io/part-of: \"kiali-operator\"\n      annotations:\n        prometheus.io/scrape: \"true\"\n    spec:\n      serviceAccountName: kiali-operator\n      containers:\n      - name: operator\n        image: \"quay.io/kiali/kiali-operator:latest\"\n        imagePullPolicy: Always\n        args:\n        - \"--zap-log-level=info\"\n        - \"--leader-election-id=kiali-operator\"\n        securityContext:\n          allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n          privileged: false\n          runAsNonRoot: true\n        volumeMounts:\n        - mountPath: /tmp/ansible-operator/runner\n          name: runner\n        env:\n        - name: WATCH_NAMESPACE\n          value: kiali-operator\n        - name: POD_NAME\n          valueFrom:\n            fieldRef:\n              fieldPath: metadata.name\n        - name: POD_NAMESPACE\n          valueFrom:\n            fieldRef:\n              fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n        - name: ALLOW_AD_HOC_KIALI_NAMESPACE\n          value: \"true\"\n        - name: ALLOW_AD_HOC_KIALI_IMAGE\n          value: \"true\"\n        - name: PROFILE_TASKS_TASK_OUTPUT_LIMIT\n          value: \"100\"\n        - name: ANSIBLE_DEBUG_LOGS\n          value: \"true\"\n        - name: ANSIBLE_VERBOSITY_KIALI_KIALI_IO\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: ANSIBLE_CONFIG\n          value: \"/opt/ansible/ansible-profiler.cfg\"\n        ports:\n        - name: http-metrics\n          containerPort: 8080\n      volumes:\n      - name: runner\n        emptyDir: {}\n      affinity:\n        {}\n...\n\nNOTES:\nWelcome to Kiali! For more details on Kiali, see: https://kiali.io\n\nThe Kiali Operator [v1.37.0-SNAPSHOT] has been installed in namespace [kiali-operator]. It will be ready soon.\nYou have elected not to install a Kiali CR. You must first install a Kiali CR in the operator watch namespace [kiali-operator] before you can access Kiali.\n\nIf you ever want to uninstall the Kiali Operator, remember to delete the Kiali CR first before uninstalling the operator to give the operator a chance to uninstall and remove all the Kiali Server resources.\n\n(Helm: Chart=[kiali-operator], Release=[kiali-operator], Version=[1.37.0-SNAPSHOT])",[0m
